The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, March 27, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, March 26: The rate of inflation fell to 4.78 per cent for the second week of March, marginally lower than the 4.91 per cent recorded in the previous week and 6.0 per cent in the week ended March 15, 2003. However, this decline is due in large measure to the governments diktat to the national oil companies to hold the price of petro goods despite rising international oil prices. 																								 New Delhi, March 26: The government today approved 34 foreign direct investment proposals worth Rs 30.98 crore, including the Rs 17-crore plan of IndusInd International Holdings to acquire equity from the secondary market. Also, Singapore-based Nico J Morgan will bring in Rs 4 crore for transferring shares from residents to non-residents.																								 Calcutta, March 26: The promoters of BSL Limited, formerly Bhilwara Synthetics Limited, have increased their stake in the company to 45.91 per cent of the total paid up capital by purchasing 65,000 shares from the market. 																								 New Delhi, March 26: The Reserve Bank today asked tax-payers to remit their income tax dues well in advance at its counters or in special branches of SBI, HDFC Bank, ICICI Bank, IDBI Bank and UTI Bank to avoid last minute rush. It becomes difficult for the banks to cope with the pressure of receipts although additional counters to the maximum extent possible are provided for the purpose, the RBI said.																								 New Delhi, March 26: India today said it was trying to form a group, including developing countries like Brazil and China to hold negotiations on steel subsidy agreement. We are trying to forge a group primarily with Brazil, China and Egypt to negotiate with OECD countries on steel subsidy agreement, joint secretary (steel) J. P. Singh said today. 																								 Mumbai, March 26: Trading in Digital GlobalSoft shares will stop on BSE from March 29. It will be removed from the exchanges records on March 31. The scrip will be replaced by United Phosphorous in the BSE-100 index and BSE-200 index while the newly listed Petronet LNG will replace it in BSE-500.
